In this article, President Trump discusses various topics related to the COVID-19 pandemic. He mentions that the country wants to get back to work and praises the efforts of doctors, nurses, and first responders. He also mentions the Comfort ship, which is being sent to New York four weeks ahead of schedule and is stocked with supplies. President Trump expresses his satisfaction with the job done by 3M and states that there will be enough ventilators. He indicates that he may use the Defense Production Act (DPA) again in the future if needed. The President mentions that he is considering a quarantine for New York, New Jersey, and certain parts of Connecticut due to the high number of cases in those areas. He emphasizes that he is having a good dialogue with Governor Cuomo and is providing assistance to New York and New Jersey. President Trump concludes by mentioning that the quarantine would be enforceable if implemented.